<front>
<div type="abstract"><head>Rat an Windsheim</head><p>Der Rat dankt für die Auskunft über Rothenburg ob der Tauber.</p>
</div>
<!--This div could possibly contain the analytic portion of the edition.-->
<div type="linguisticAnalysis"><ab><w join="" lemma="" msd="" part="" pos=""><fLib><f name=" "/></fLib></w></ab></div>
</front>
<body><div type="diplomatic"><pb facs="#facs_516" id="257v"/><!--The following div is the container for the adress lines of the letter.-->
<div type="addressee"><ab facs="#facs_516_r1l1"><expan>Winſh<ex>eim</ex></expan> </ab>
</div>
<!-- This div contains the letter itselfs. Additions to the text are contained in <add/> elements, struck text in <hi> elements with the attribute 'strikethrough' set to true. -->
<div type="content"><ab facs="#facs_516_r1l2"><expan>Lıeb<ex>e</ex>n</expan> <expan>fr<ex>ewnde</ex></expan> / Ewr briefe vnd als Jr vns <expan>embot<ex>e</ex>n</expan> habt </ab>
<ab facs="#facs_516_r1l3"><expan>hab<ex>e</ex>n</expan> wir vvol <expan>v<ex>er</ex>nomen</expan> / vnd <expan>danke<ex>n</ex></expan> des <expan>ewr<ex>er</ex></expan> <expan>frewntſch<ex>aft</ex></expan> </ab>
<ab facs="#facs_516_r1l5">mit <expan>gancʒe<ex>m</ex></expan> fleiſʒe / vnd wo es <expan>vnſ<ex>er</ex>n</expan> güten 
<add><ab facs="#facs_516_r1l4">frewnden </ab></add> den <expan>vo<ex>n</ex></expan> <expan>Rot<ex>emburg</ex></expan> </ab>
<ab facs="#facs_516_r1l6">wol gieng / Das hörten vnd ſehen wir cʒemal <expan>g<ex>er</ex>ne</expan> / . </ab>
<ab facs="#facs_516_r1l7">vnd <expan>bıt<ex>en</ex></expan> <expan>ew<ex>r</ex></expan> <expan>erſamk<ex>eit</ex></expan> was Jr auch fürbas trefflichs </ab>
<ab facs="#facs_516_r1l8">gewar würdt <expan>od<ex>er</ex></expan> <expan>v<ex>er</ex>nemt</expan> / daʒ Jr vns das <expan>ab<ex>er</ex></expan> <expan>cʒewıſſ<ex>en</ex></expan> </ab>
<ab facs="#facs_516_r1l9">tün wöllet als wir ew des vor auch <expan>gepet<ex>e</ex>n</expan> <expan>hab<ex>e</ex>n</expan> </ab>
<ab facs="#facs_516_r1l10"><expan>Deſgleich<ex>e</ex>n</expan> wir gen ew auch <expan>g<ex>er</ex>n</expan> tün wöllen / vnd vvo </ab>
<ab facs="#facs_516_r1l11">wir <expan>ewr<ex>er</ex></expan> <expan>frewntſch<ex>aft</ex></expan> / lıeb vnd dienſt <expan>beweiſe<ex>n</ex></expan> <expan>möht<ex>e</ex>n</expan> </ab>
<ab facs="#facs_516_r1l12">das <expan>tet<ex>e</ex>n</expan> vvir <expan>allcʒ<ex>eit</ex></expan> mit vvillen <expan>g<ex>er</ex>ne</expan> / . <expan>Dat<ex>um</ex></expan> <expan>f<ex>er</ex>ıa</expan> vj̃ </ab>
<ab facs="#facs_516_r1l13"><expan>p<ex>oſt</ex></expan> <expan>Natı<ex>uita</ex><hi rend="sup">t<ex>is</ex></hi></expan> Marie / </ab>
</div>
</div><div type="regularised"><pb facs="#facs_516" id="257v"/><!--The following div is the container for the adress lines of the letter.-->
<div type="addressee">
<ab><expan>Winsh<ex>eim</ex></expan>
</ab>
</div>
<!-- This div contains the letter itselfs. Additions to the text are contained in <add/> elements, struck text in <hi> elements with the attribute 'strikethrough' set to true. -->
<div type="content">
<ab><expan>Lieb<ex>e</ex>n</expan>
<expan>fr<ex>eunde</ex></expan>, ewr briefe und als
                                                ir uns <expan>embot<ex>e</ex>n</expan> habt,
                                                  <expan>hab<ex>e</ex>n</expan> wir wol
                                                  <expan>v<ex>er</ex>nomen</expan> und
                                                  <expan>danke<ex>n</ex></expan> des
                                                  <expan>ewr<ex>er</ex></expan>
<expan>frewntsch<ex>aft</ex></expan> mit
                                                  <expan>gancze<ex>m</ex></expan> fleisze; und wo es
                                                  <expan>uns<ex>er</ex>n</expan> güten
                                                  <add>frewnden</add>, den
                                                  <expan>vo<ex>n</ex></expan>
<expan>Rot<ex>emburg</ex></expan>, wol gieng, das
                                                hörten und sehen wir czemal
                                                  <expan>g<ex>er</ex>ne</expan>. Und
                                                  <expan>bit<ex>en</ex></expan>
<expan>ew<ex>r</ex></expan>
<expan>ersamk<ex>eit</ex></expan>, was ir auch
                                                fürbas trefflichs gewar würdt
                                                  <expan>od<ex>er</ex></expan>
<expan>v<ex>er</ex>nemt</expan>, daz ir uns das
                                                  <expan>ab<ex>er</ex></expan>
<expan>cze wiss<ex>en</ex></expan> tün wöllet, als
                                                wir ew des vor auch <expan>gepet<ex>e</ex>n</expan>
<expan>hab<ex>e</ex>n</expan>,
                                                  <expan>desgleich<ex>e</ex>n</expan> wir gen ew
                                                auch <expan>g<ex>er</ex>n</expan> tün wöllen. Und wo
                                                wir <expan>ewr<ex>er</ex></expan>
<expan>frewntsch<ex>aft</ex></expan> lieb und dienst
                                                  <expan>beweise<ex>n</ex></expan>
<expan>möht<ex>e</ex>n</expan>, das
                                                  <expan>tet<ex>e</ex>n</expan> wir
                                                  <expan>allcz<ex>eit</ex></expan> mit willen
                                                  <expan>g<ex>er</ex>ne</expan>.
                                                  <expan>Dat<ex>um</ex></expan>
<expan>f<ex>er</ex>ia</expan> vi
                                                  <expan>p<ex>ost</ex></expan>
<expan>nati<ex>vita</ex><hi rend="sup">t<ex>is</ex></hi></expan> Marie.</ab>
</div>
